	<page>
		<exercise xml:id="truck-grass-linear-ineq">
			<introduction>
				<p>
					A truck hauling bags of grass seed weighs 3,900 pounds when it is empty. Each bag of seed it carries weighs 4.2 pounds. The equation for the gross weight <m>W</m> pounds is <me>W = 3{,}900 + 4.2B</me> for <m>B</m> bags of grass seed. 
					<em>
						(Story also appears in
						<xref ref="truck-grass-arithmetic-operations" />, 
						<xref ref="truck-grass-first-look-linear" />, and  
						<xref ref="truck-grass-solving-linear" />)
					</em>
				</p>
			</introduction>
			<task workspace="1.25in">
				<statement>
					<p>
						The state highways have a 18,000 pound gross weight limit. How many bags of grass seed can the truck haul? Set up and solve an appropriate inequality.
					</p>
				</statement>
			</task>
			<task>
				<statement>
					<p>
						Record your answer to part (a) in the table and graph the function.
					</p>
					<tabular bottom="minor" top="minor">
